parameters:
Clea (I can't go back until I talk to the noble Pido from
the Senate)

Noble Pido of the Senate, What's this? I didn't have any
plans to meet someone today.

Sister Eleo: I am Sister Eleo, who serves as a sister in the
village of Irini. I have come to request Caron-sama's
permission to build a tavern.

Noble Pido of the Senate: Oh, I see... So you're the rumored
Dragon Slayer over there.
Clea: Nice to meet you for the first time.

Noble Pido of the Senate: Hahaha, appearances can be
deceiving. So what brings you, the Dragon Slayers, to me?

Sister Eleo: I have come regarding the matter of alcohol.
Please allow it to be distributed in the village of Irini as
well!

Noble Pido of the Senate: Hahaha, so that's why you've
come!? It seems the instructions haven't been accurately
conveyed...

Noble Pido of the Senate: I don't mind, go ahead and open a
tavern or whatever. I'll give instructions to have alcohol
delivered as a celebration from me as well.
Sister Eleo: T-Thank you very much!

Sister Sophia: Excuse me... but it sounded like there was a
special reason for the prohibition, is that correct?

Noble Pido of the Senate: You all must know as well, drugs
and alcohol... many of them were a source of funding for the
thieves of Camps.

Sister Sophia: So if you've given permission, does that
mean--

Noble Pido of the Senate: You have quite the sharp
intuition. We are preparing to eradicate those thieves once
and for all.

Noble Pido of the Senate: It won't be immediate, but Atu is
slow to act... Once he starts moving, it's like a raging
fire.

Thief Nora: Eh, does that mean the Emma Thieves are also the
target...?

Noble Pido of the Senate: Ah, of course. I thought you came
here today for that negotiation.

Noble Pido of the Senate: No matter what you say, it's
already been decided.

Noble Pido of the Senate: But before that, tell me, young
lady of the clergy, what is your name?
Sister Sophia: My name is Sophia, Lord Pido.

Noble Pido of the Senate: I see, I see. Such beauty, such
physique, it's a waste for you to remain as a sister.
Noble Pido of the Senate: How about becoming my woman?

Noble Pido of the Senate: That's a good attitude, it's
piqued my interest even more!

Noble Pido of the Senate: This is the end. I have dealt with
this sudden visit up until now, so show some respect.

Noble Pido of the Senate: Hey, investigate the background of
that clergywoman.

Noble Pido of the Senate: Don't misunderstand. This is not
my usual investigation of women.

Noble Pido of the Senate: That woman... She shouldn't be a
sister, but I feel like I've seen her somewhere before...
She might be useful for something.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: I should have finished my
business. There is nothing more for me to tell you.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, you've come well! There
are three people here who weren't called... well, it's not
too bad.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Never mind their small and
slender figures, I wouldn't mind gathering them all as my
mistresses.

Mage Relm: I absolutely, absolutely won't become your
mistress! I won't tolerate being treated as an outcast!

Clea: I'm angry that you tried to use Sophia-san and mocked
our friend.

Thief Nora: Me too! I won't forgive what was done to the
Emma Thief Guild... absolutely not!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: What do you think I should do
with the guards that you all managed to get through?

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Only Sophia has business here.
Shall I let her hear the response to the letter she
delivered?

Priestess Sophia: I... thought that I would be willing to
become a mistress for Prince Rex.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, that's fine! Making him
the king, you being his lover, is there a greater
contradiction than this!?

Noble of the Senate, Pido: To think that the former torturer
of the Shadow Division would become a queen... hahaha, it's
a joke even funnier than the high-class prostitute Caron!

Priestess Sophia: Torturer Alicia would probably think so
too...

Priestess Sophia: But! Priestess Sophia! The people who
believe in Priestess Sophia!

Priestess Sophia: I absolutely won't forgive that...! That's
why I can't become your mistress, absolutely can't!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, I see. I've become even
more eager, even more determined to take it away.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, there would be no greater
pleasure than embracing you in front of Rex!

Clea: It's good to be lowly, I can fight without any
hesitation.
Clea: Let's go on a rampage!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Impressive skills! As expected of
the Adventurer's Guild, as expected of a Dragon Slayer!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: But, what about the next
opponent?

Noble of the Senate, Pido: They are the guards of the
campus, they should understand the meaning of turning their
blades towards the soldiers of the empire, right?

Noble of the Senate, Pido: I'll ask again... Do you have any
intention of becoming my mistress?
Clea: I refuse! Sophia-san made a promise with us.

Cleric Sophia: I'm sorry... Even if it means breaking the
promise twice, I just can't think of any other way.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, what a clever woman!
Sophia is the only one who knows the way to salvation!
Noble of the Senate, Pido: Now, become mine.
Clea: Sophia-san, nobody wants that kind of thing--
Clea: Ugh... Why... Please, I'm begging you!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: What a comfortable embrace. Such
a wasted body on a spineless prince.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: And besides... It's most charming
that you truly despise me.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Never let your guard down. Those
people can abandon their own interests... They will attack
without hesitation, you know?
Cleric Sophia: Will this satisfy you? Please release them.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: I will keep that promise, but it
would be boring without an audience, don't you think?

Cleric Sophia: Prince Rex-sama!? Please run away, please get
away from here!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Honestly, who am I giving orders
to? Whether it's you or Caron, it doesn't matter to me.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Whoever controls this fertile
land of Campus will come closer to ruling the empire as a
king.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: You are not in a position to give
me orders. You are in a position to beg for cooperation.

Cleric Sophia: That's right... Becoming a king is a
difficult path, and this is just one of those challenges.

Cleric Sophia: I have been loved enough. My feelings for you
will never change, no matter what happens.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, what touching words! I
know many women who have said the same and abandoned their
husbands.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: After all, women are attracted to
strong men. Kindness has no value or meaning in front of
that.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Every man has a beast in his
heart without exception. What is your beast, is it a beast
worthy of aspiring to be a king?

Prince Rex: M-My... the beast in my heart... that person...
that monster...!
Clea: Sophia-san said that Prince Rex is a very kind person!

Clea: Kindness is not just a temporary convenience for the
other person!

Clea: It's when my father stood up against the dragon and my
mother protected me with her life!

Clea: Please don't fight now...! Just when exactly... are
you going to fight!?

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Just when I thought you screamed
out of nowhere... you're such a troublesome man.
Prince Rex: Let her go... she belongs to me.

Prince Rex: Didn't you hear? Noble of the Senate, Pido...
Let go of what belongs to me right now.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hmph, don't make me say it again.
Your position is--

Prince Rex: Are you making me say the same thing four times
to the future emperor of the empire?
Noble of the Senate, Pido: Tch!

Prince Rex: Noble of the Senate, Pido, I know that you are
colluding with the nobles of Oros.

Prince Rex: I will grant you the honor of cooperating with
me.
Noble of the Senate, Pido: W-What about me...?!

Prince Rex: This is the last time, don't make me say the
same thing twice.

Prince Rex: Noble of the Senate, Pido, will you accept this
honor?
Noble of the Senate, Pido: Bring me pen and paper...

Mansion Butler: If it's a letter, I can be your ghostwriter,
sir.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: It's a testament, I'll write it
now.
Mansion Butler: Are you saying Queen Caron will win?!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: If Caron wins... she will never
forgive me for siding with Rex.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: If Rex wins... I will be killed
by the beast that resides within that man.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Even the father of that man, who
was called the Immaculate King, had a monster in his heart.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: It is said that the father of
that man, who is not to be taken lightly, had an ogre in his
heart due to his ferocity.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Rex, who keeps a dragon in his
heart, I wonder if I have broken that cage...

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Rex might become a monstrous king
who surpasses his father and destroys everything in the
empire.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble of the Senate, Pido: You fought well, but it's a
shame. Well, even if you had won, it would have only meant
calling the imperial soldiers.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Well, Sophia, there's no need for
me to tell you what you should do from now on, right?

Noble of the Senate, Pido: It's no longer just about the
prince. The lives of important friends who call you Sophia
are also in your hands.

Clea: P-Please, you don't have to worry about us. Just you,
Sophia-san, please escape from here...
Clea: Please... keep the promise you made with me... ugh...

Priestess Sophia: I'm sorry, Clea-chan, but I... can't
abandon all of you.

Priestess Sophia: And besides, Prince Rex... I still believe
that he is there.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Hahaha, this is perfect! I will
obtain whatever I desire!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Once again, I have emerged
victorious.
Prince Rex: Haa...haa... Let go of Sophia-san!

Noble of the Senate, Pido: I've been waiting for this. The
greatest stage requires the greatest audience.

Priestess Sophia (Prince Rex has come! This must be because
he came for me as his lover...)
Priestess Sophia (You came to save me!)

Priestess Sophia (I'm happy... even though it's such a
foolish situation... I'm truly... happy)

Priestess Sophia (Prince Rex mustered up the courage and
stood before this man... for my sake)

Priestess Sophia (I truly love Prince Rex, even though I
strongly realize that I am a woman)
後order：アダルトシーン875再生
Would you like to skip the adult scene?
後order：アダルトシーン875再生

Would you like to retry the battle?※ If you choose No, it
will result in a game over.

Noble of the Senate, Pido: Rex might become a monstrous mad
king who surpasses his father and destroys everything in the
empire.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble of the Senate, Pido: As someone who swears loyalty to
Prince Rex, I do not wish to make enemies of dragons.

Noble Pido of the Senate: I'm glad you accepted the request.
Actually, it was intended for you, and the others were
turned away at the gate--

Noble Pido of the Senate: First, let me apologize. I
understand! I apologize for the many past rudenesses.

Noble Pido of the Senate: We don't expect you to forget
everything and cooperate with Prince Rex, but we would like
you to hear us out.

Clea: First, let me confirm. This request is not intended to
deceive us, right?

Noble Pido of the Senate: Of course, it is a formal request.
There is a special reason why we want to ask for your help.

Noble Pido of the Senate: There is no way Caron doesn't know
about my loyalty to Prince Rex.

Noble Pido of the Senate: If we were to mobilize the guards
of the campus in such a situation, it might lead to a battle
that Prince Rex does not desire.
Cleric Sophia: I appreciate your wonderful consideration.

Noble Pido of the Senate: I apologize... The reason why I
didn't directly request the Adventurer's Guild, which has
been particularly rude to you, is the same.

Clea: I understand, but the attack on the thieves should
have been stopped, right?
Thief Nora: That's right, I will definitely not forget!

Noble Pido of the Senate: I apologize for the incident with
the Emma Thieves! If we continue like this, the sun will set
before we get to the main topic...!

Noble Pido of the Senate: Regarding this request...
Actually, we received a message from the High Priestess of
Imiserinos.

Noble Pido of the Senate: It is extremely unusual for me to
be directly approached like this... The request is to save
the leader of the Loparo Plunderers.
Clea: Does it mean to rescue them...?

Noble Pido of the Senate: I don't understand the true
intention, so I want you to confirm the details directly
with the High Priestess.

Noble Pido of the Senate: We have dispatched a guide to the
hideout of the Loparo Plunderers at the Atmis Temple.

Clea: Understood. I won't forget about the past, but I will
do my best.

Noble Pido of the Senate: Sigh... I will never be your enemy
again, never!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble Pido of the Senate: Since the shrine maiden is
involved, we cannot afford to fail. And for the sake of the
campus, please make sure to carry it out without fail.
Clea: I have a report regarding the request.

Noble Pido of the Senate: I am aware of the situation.
First, let's hand over the reward for this request.

Sister Eleo: Why... is he someone who can admit his sins and
surely repent?

Noble Pido of the Senate: Sister Eleo, you should understand
as well.

Noble Pido of the Senate: The Loparo Raiders did more than
just plunder in the campus. Arson, rape, murder,
kidnapping...

Noble Pido of the Senate: His execution is determined by the
Empire's regulations, not by emotional judgment.

Noble Pido of the Senate: I understand that you are the one
who accomplished this task, but we cannot overturn the
public execution for the sake of the campus.

Noble Pido of the Senate: Please consider the people who
were taken by the Loparo Raiders as well.
Sister Eleo: In that case... please grant me one request!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Noble of the Senate, Pido: I couldn't accept all of the
requests, but I did my best to accommodate them.
